description.narrative: Capacity of WASH institutions at national and regional levels has been strengthened to plan, deliver, and monitor WASH services for 180,627 people (91,216 female, 89,411 male and 84,724 children (43,512 girls 41,212 boys)) in 67 communities, 14 schools and 02 health facilities. This was through training of WASH stakeholders on guidelines in health care facilities, review and development of WASH policies, strategies, community engagement on ending open defecation, provision of WASH facilities and response to the windstorm emergency in URR. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/12/2019
